main event: An observer reported sighting three unidentified flying objects in the sky on November 10, 1967.
interesting points: The largest object resembled a star while the other two were red and approximately two-thirds its size., The sighting lasted between 1 to 2.5 minutes., The objects flew in a straight course and disappeared rapidly., The observer noted no physical evidence or photographs of the sighting., The witness completed a questionnaire detailing their observation experience.
witness description: Dale R. Ellis, a 40-year-old high school student with no previous experience regarding U.F.O.s.
